7.1.11 - M365SR11: Lack of Independent Backup and Recovery Mechanisms
ISM controls:
•	Control: 1515; Revision: 1; Updated: Sep-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Backup of data in cloud services)
•	Control: 1516; Revision: 1; Updated: Sep-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Restoration of data in cloud services)
•	Control: 1653; Revision: 0; Updated: Dec-23; Applicability: All; OS: All (Independent verification of data integrity in cloud services)
________________________________________
Current Risk
With no third-party backup, recovery, or integrity checking mechanisms in place, Microsoft is singularly in control of the integrity and availability of agency data that resides within the M365 tenancy. This creates a single point of failure where a platform-wide outage, sophisticated ransomware attack, or accidental administrative deletion could result in permanent data loss.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
POSSIBLE	x	MAJOR	=	HIGH
________________________________________
Recommendations:
1.	Implement Independent Third-Party Backup: Procure and deploy a cloud-to-cloud backup solution (e.g., Veeam, Commvault, or AvePoint) that maintains an immutable copy of Exchange, SharePoint, OneDrive, and Teams data outside of the Microsoft ecosystem.
2.	Establish a Recovery Time Objective (RTO): Define and document formal RTO and Recovery Point Objective (RPO) targets for core SaaS services, ensuring they align with the agency's broader Business Continuity Plan (BCP).
3.	Perform Regular Restoration Testing: Conduct quarterly disaster recovery drills to verify the integrity of backed-up data and the effectiveness of the restoration process for both granular items and full-tenant scenarios.
- Treatment #1
•	Solution Architecture: Design a backup architecture that utilises a separate cloud provider (e.g., AWS S3 with Object Lock or an on-premises target) to store immutable backups, preventing a single set of compromised credentials from deleting both live data and backups.
•	Integrity Validation: Enable automated daily checksums and integrity alerts within the backup solution to detect silent data corruption or unauthorised modifications.
•	Business Continuity Integration: Update the agency Disaster Recovery Plan to include specific playbooks for "M365 Tenant Recovery" using the third-party backup tool.
________________________________________
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented.
Implementing an independent, immutable backup solution removes the reliance on Microsoft’s native "recycle bin" features and provides a fallback in the event of a catastrophic platform failure or account-wide compromise. While the consequence of a data loss event remains "Major" due to mission impact, the likelihood of permanent, unrecoverable data loss is reduced to "Rare."
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
RARE	x	MAJOR	=	MEDIUM
